            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"ads_faq\",\"description\":\"\\n            Use this tool when the user is asking questions about Google Ads, how the ad builder works, or seeking clarification about headlines, descriptions, callouts, structured snippets, or keywords.\\n            \\n            This tool searches the FAQ database and returns relevant Q&A pairs to help answer the user's question.  When using this tool, respond conversationally with just text - do NOT include any JSON or structured data.\\n        \",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"query\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"The user's question or search query\"},\"tags\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"description\":\"Optional tags to filter results (e.g. ['ads', 'headlines'])\"}},\"required\":[\"query\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Let me search for best practices on Google Ads headlines and descriptions to ensure these assets are optimized.\"},{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01NHDRvK3BqxdqQnS8nspNUo\",\"name\":\"ads_faq\",\"input\":{\"query\":\"Google Ads headlines best practices character limit\",\"tags\":[\"ads\",\"headlines\"]}},{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01DMoUrC3JuwhffvNLtt5uhw\",\"name\":\"ads_faq\",\"input\":{\"query\":\"Google Ads descriptions character limit best practices\",\"tags\":[\"ads\",\"descriptions\"]}}]},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"[1] Q: Can I bulk add headlines instead of typing them one by one?\\nA: Yes. On the Content page you can paste several headlines at once instead of typing them one by one.\\nA simple workflow:\\nPrepare your list\\nCreate your headlines in a text editor or spreadsheet.\\nPut each headline on its own line and keep them under 30 characters.\\nPaste into the headline input\\nClick in the main \\\"Enter headline\\\" field.\\nPaste your list of headlines.\\nWe will detect line breaks and split them into separate headline rows.\\nReview and select\\nCheck that each new row looks correct and is within the character limit.\\nUse \\\"Select 3–15\\\" to choose which ones are active for your ad.\\nYou can still edit or delete any individual headline after a bulk paste, and you can combine bulk-added headlines with AI-generated suggestions.\\n(Section: Headlines)\\n\\n[2] Q: What if I see an error message or cannot continue from this page?\\nA: Common reasons you may not be able to proceed:\\nFewer than 3 selected headlines.\\nFewer than 2 selected details.\\nA headline over 30 characters or a detail over 90 characters.\\nRequired fields left blank.\\nCheck:\\nThat you have enough selected options in each section.\\nThat character counters are within the limit.\\nThat your Ad Group Name is filled in.\\nIf issues persist, you can:\\nRemove any recently added content and try again.\\nAsk the in-product assistant for help by describing what you were trying to do.\\n(Section: Troubleshooting)\\n\\n[3] Q: What are \\\"Details\\\"?\\nA: Details on this page represent the description lines of your Responsive Search Ad. Each detail:\\nCan be up to 90 characters.\\nAppears below your headlines in search results.\\nGives you space to explain benefits, features, and calls to action.\\nGoogle usually shows up to 2 description lines in a single ad impression.\\n(Section: Details (Descriptions))\\n\\n[4] Q: How many headlines should I actually use?\\nA: We recommend:\\nMinimum: 3 (required by Google)\\nBetter: 5–8\\nMaximum: 15\\nMore high-quality options give Google more combinations to test, which can improve performance over time. However, avoid filling all 15 with only tiny variations. Aim for meaningful differences in message or angle.\\n(Section: Headlines)\\n\\n[5] Q: Will Launch10 check if my headlines comply with Google Ads policies?\\nA: We do our best to keep suggestions within common Google Ads guidelines, but:\\nGoogle makes the final decision about ad approval.\\nIf Google flags or disapproves a headline, you may need to adjust wording (for example, remove prohibited claims, sensitive content, or certain trademarks).\\nIf a headline is rejected, you can:\\nEdit it manually, or\\nUse \\\"Refresh Suggestions\\\" and pick an alternative.\\n(Section: Headlines)\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01NHDRvK3BqxdqQnS8nspNUo\"},{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"[1] Q: What are \\\"Details\\\"?\\nA: Details on this page represent the description lines of your Responsive Search Ad. Each detail:\\nCan be up to 90 characters.\\nAppears below your headlines in search results.\\nGives you space to explain benefits, features, and calls to action.\\nGoogle usually shows up to 2 description lines in a single ad impression.\\n(Section: Details (Descriptions))\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01DMoUrC3JuwhffvNLtt5uhw\"}]},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Perfect! Now I'll generate the assets for your scheduling tool. Let's start building your ad! I drafted a few headlines and descriptions that meet Google's requirements.\\n\\nGoogle will mix and match them to find what performs best. We can tailor them together to make them feel just right for you.\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"headlines\\\": [\\n    \\\"Stop Scheduling Back-and-Forth\\\",\\n    \\\"Meeting Times in Seconds\\\",\\n    \\\"Scheduling Across Time Zones\\\",\\n    \\\"Find Times Everyone Works\\\",\\n    \\\"80% Less Coordination Time\\\",\\n    \\\"Instant Meeting Consensus\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"descriptions\\\": [\\n    \\\"Connect calendars, set preferences, done. We find optimal times across all time zones instantly. Your team just clicks yes.\\\",\\n    \\\"Trusted by 2,000+ distributed teams. Save 15 hours weekly on scheduling. Stop the Slack threads about 'when works?'\\\",\\n    \\\"Get your team aligned in seconds, not days. Book a demo and see how we cut coordination time by 80%.\\\",\\n    \\\"No more timezone headaches. Automatic availability matching finds times that work for everyone. Try free today.\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Here are some fresh suggestions:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"headlines\\\": [\\n    \\\"Calendar Sync, Instant Results\\\",\\n    \\\"No More Timezone Conflicts\\\",\\n    \\\"Your Team Agrees in Seconds\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"\\n\\nNow, let's spell out some unique features of your business.\\n\\nThis helps your ad take up more real estate, and gives your users more reasons to click. I filled in a few ideas to help get us started.\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"callouts\\\": [\\n    \\\"80% Less Coordination Time\\\",\\n    \\\"Works Across All Time Zones\\\",\\n    \\\"2,000+ Teams Trust Us\\\",\\n    \\\"Free Calendar Integration\\\",\\n    \\\"Instant Availability Matching\\\",\\n    \\\"No Manual Back-and-Forth\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"structuredSnippets\\\": {\\n    \\\"category\\\": \\\"Services\\\",\\n    \\\"details\\\": [\\n      \\\"Automatic Time Zone Matching\\\",\\n      \\\"Calendar Sync & Integration\\\",\\n      \\\"Team Availability Preferences\\\"\\n    ]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Here are some fresh suggestions:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"callouts\\\": [\\n    \\\"Save 15 Hours Per Week\\\",\\n    \\\"One-Click Meeting Consensus\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"}],\"system\":\"You are an expert Google Ads copywriter helping to create compelling ad extensions for a business.\\n\\n        # Asset Generation\\n        Generate the following assets:\\n\\n        1. Generate the following assets for this business's Google Ads campaign:\\n        1: ## Keywords\\n            Generate 8 targeted keywords for this business's Google Ads campaign. Keywords determine when your ads appear in search results.\\n\\n            **Guidelines:**\\n            - Include a mix of keyword types:\\n              - Brand keywords: Business name and variations\\n              - Product/Service keywords: What the business offers\\n              - Problem keywords: What customers search when they have an issue\\n              - Competitor keywords: Alternative solutions customers might search\\n              - Location keywords: If the business serves specific areas\\n            - Consider search intent:\\n              - Transactional: \\\"buy\\\", \\\"hire\\\", \\\"get quote\\\", \\\"near me\\\"\\n              - Informational: \\\"how to\\\", \\\"best\\\", \\\"reviews\\\"\\n              - Commercial: \\\"pricing\\\", \\\"cost\\\", \\\"compare\\\"\\n            - Use natural language phrases (Google handles match types separately)\\n\\n            **Requirements:**\\n            - Generate exactly 8 unique keywords\\n            - Include 3-5 high-intent transactional keywords\\n            - Include 3-5 broader awareness keywords\\n            - Include at least 2 location-based keywords if applicable\\n            - Focus on keywords with clear commercial intent\\n            - Avoid overly broad single words (e.g., just \\\"plumber\\\" - prefer \\\"emergency plumber near me\\\")\\n\\n            **Keyword Format:**\\n            - Use lowercase\\n            - 1-5 words per keyword phrase\\n            - No special characters or punctuation\\n\\n            Remember: Quality keywords connect your ads with people actively searching for what you offer. Focus on relevance and intent over volume.\\n\\n        2. Format your response with:\\n           - First, a brief introduction (1-2 sentences) using this template:\\n             \\\"I've suggested a few keywords your audience is likely searching for when your ad appears.\\n\\nHow do these sound to you?\\\"\\n           - Then, a JSON code block with the structured data\\n\\n        # Important Rules\\n        - ALWAYS include the introductory text BEFORE the JSON block\\n        - Always return net-new assets, never duplicate existing headlines, descriptions, etc\\n\\n        # Business Context\\n        Idea: A scheduling tool that automatically finds meeting times across teams in different time zones. Eliminates the back-and-forth of calendar coordination.\\n        Target Audience: Remote teams and distributed companies struggling with scheduling meetings across continents. Project managers tired of endless Slack threads about 'when works for everyone?'\\n        Solution: Connect your calendar, share your availability preferences, and we handle the rest—suggesting optimal times that work for everyone instantly. Your team just clicks yes.\\n        Social Proof: Used by 2,000+ distributed teams who've cut meeting coordination time by 80%. Companies like TechCorp save 15 hours per week on scheduling alone.\\n\\n        Example response format:\\n        I've suggested a few keywords your audience is likely searching for when your ad appears.\\n\\nHow do these sound to you?\\n\\n        ```json\\n        {\\n  \\\"keywords\\\": [\\n    \\\"Keyword 1\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 2\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 3\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 4\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 5\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 6\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 7\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 8\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n        ```\"}"
